ENTRY       EC 1.12.1.5                 Enzyme
NAME        hydrogen dehydrogenase [NAD(P)+];
            hydrogenase II (ambiguous)
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on hydrogen as donor;
            With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
SYSNAME     hydrogen:NAD(P)+ oxidoreductase
REACTION    H2 + NAD(P)+ = H+ + NAD(P)H [RN:R00700 R07181]
ALL_REAC    R00700 R07181
SUBSTRATE   H2 [CPD:C00282];
            NAD+ [CPD:C00003];
            NADP+ [CPD:C00006]
PRODUCT     H+ [CPD:C00080];
            NADH [CPD:C00004];
            NADPH [CPD:C00005]
COMMENT     A nickel, iron, iron-sulfur protein. The enzyme from the archaeon Pyrococcus furiosus is part of a heterotetrameric complex where the alpha and delta subunits function as a hydrogenase while the beta and gamma subunits function as sulfur reductase (EC 1.12.98.4, sulfhydrogenase). Different from EC 1.12.1.3, hydrogen dehydrogenase (NADP+).
